e.c: CP: adjectives that form the comparative and superlative forms with more and the most respectively
CP: adjectives that add -er and -est to form the comparative and superlative forms
CP: adjectives that delete -y and add -ier and -iest to form the comparative and superlative forms
CP: adjectives that finish in -y and directly add -er and -est to form the comparative and superlative forms
CP: adjectives that either delete the -y and add -ier and -iest to form the comparative and superlative forms or directly add -er and -est (LR)
CP: adjectives that finish in -e and therefore only add -r and -st to form the comparative and superlative forms
CP: adjectives that finish in -g and add -ger and -gest to form the comparative and superlative forms
CP: adjectives that finish in -t and add -ter and -test to form the comparative and superlative forms
CP: adjectives that finish in -n and add -ner and -nest to form the comparative and superlative forms
CP: adjectives that finish in -m and add -mer and -mest to form the comparative and superlative forms
CP: adjectives that may form the comparative and superlative forms either with more and the most or adding -er and -est (LR) respectively
